Today, Vice President Harris and the Office of Gun Violence Prevention convened 100 state legislators to announce the Safer States Initiative, aimed at reducing gun violence. The initiative highlights key actions that states can take, such as establishing offices focused on gun violence prevention, supporting survivors and victims, and implementing industry accountability and standards. The Justice Department also announced the publication of two model bills for safe gun storage and reporting of lost and stolen firearms. Georgia Congresswoman Lucy McBath emphasized the need for federal, state, and local action to protect communities from gun violence.